          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "The fogfisher constantly exudes an aura of fog. All creatures within the aura become concealed, and all creatures outside the fog become concealed to creatures within it.",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 5,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "8ca8a0ac0e16b3c136f09ca48d8578bb",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Air",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 452,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Effects with the air trait either manipulate or conjure air. Those that manipulate air have no effect in a vacuum or an area without air. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of air or have a connection to magical air.   \n  \nPlanes with this trait consist mostly of open spaces and air of various levels of turbulence, though they also contain rare islands of floating stone and other elements and energies. Air planes usually have breathable atmospheres, though they might include clouds of acidic or toxic gas. Earth creatures often find themselves at a disadvantage within air planes, as there\u2019s little solid ground for them to gain their bearings, which tends to at least make them uncomfortable.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 206,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "5315505cfd3f3ba2685e9747898193b2",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Aura",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 453,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An aura is an emanation that continually ebbs out from you, affecting creatures within a certain radius. Aura can also refer to the magical signature of an item.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 134,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Primal",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 460,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
